Tunde Oyekola A Kwara State Magistrates’ Court presided by Bio Saliu, has sentenced three violators of lockdown order of the state government over coronavirus pandemic to one month community service. The offenders – Amos Phillip, Babangida Dontatin and Baroye Abel, who are sawmill operators –  are to sweep premises of the Kwara State High Court for 30 days between 9am and 1pm starting Thursday (today). The three accused were alleged to have engaged in commercial activities in disobedience of the executive order restricting movement of people within the state. The accused pleaded guilty to the charges read to them in court. The magistrate, in his ruling, pronounced them guilty of the offences and convicted them to one month non residential imprisonment of engagement in community service of sweeping the High Court premises. He told the convicts that failure to comply with the judgment would be another offence, saying that the community service would be supervised by officers of the Nigeria Correctional Services. Copyright PUNCH.
